{
  "texts": [
    "Clinical images and visualizationIt can be challenging to educate about various important disorders and conditions without the use of high-quality medical images.",
    "Confidentiality concerns, especially when facial features are involved, can limit the use of traditional patient images [86].",
    "Text-to-image generative AI algorithms are capable of producing high-quality, unique images based on text prompts by employing learnt probability distributions rather than using pre-existing ones [22].",
    "Such tools can make it easier to obtain high-quality imagery for medical education.",
    "Using this strategy, we can provide visual content whose distribution on the web or social media platforms does not breach patients' privacy."
  ]
}